f=Brand Studio/nate/operational/skill/nate-skill-routing.md · p=Nate's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/nate-commands.md`. · h2:Where Identity Fits=Nate identity spark holds Brand Studio's. Universal-only principles. · h2:The Loop=`funnel-analysis        (AIM — find the leaky bucket; ends in recommended experiments) \· \| \· v \· experiment-backlog     (QUEUE — ICE-scored, capacity-honest, pre-registered; the discipline) \· \|` · h2:Handoff Rules=**funnel-analysis backlog**: recommended experiment enters intake falsifiable hypothesis; biggest leak standing first candidate., **backlog ab-test-analysis**: pre-registration enforces sibling's math *before* launch; analysis delivers verdict after. One discipline, two moments., **muse nate**: idea intake. **kai nate**: instrumentation funnel data in; results scorecard; unmeasurable tests blocked, instrumentation need routes kai., **Graduation**: channel wins rio (standing campaigns); content/hook wins pulse's register; copy wins lena; product/site wins owning surface (vista's roadmap it's feature work)., **board**: experiment spend beyond envelope gates like any spend. **spark**: experiment *creative* gates like any creative test variant gate exemption., **vista boundary**: rice-prioritization ranks roadmap features; nate's ICE ranks growth experiments different altitude; graduated win implies feature work crosses vista's queue. · h2:Precedence="Where losing users" funnel. "What test next add idea" backlog. "Is significant win" ab-test-analysis. Ambiguous aim, queue, judge? · f=data funnel runs operator-supplied numbers descriptions (estimation labeled); instrumentation blocked status, routed kai; urgency skips queue, never discipline.